summary: Why do many Avengers fanfic paint Nick Fury as an asshole?
body:
Why do many Avengers fanfic paint Nick Fury as an asshole?

I know he’s a secretive bastard, but he’s much nicer than how most fanfic authors describe. In my opinion they either do not understand his character at all, or just want somebody acting like a jerk to make their bias looks cooler. I really like this grumpy exasperated spy boss, and hate to see him got portrayed as a jerk

summary:
It was the final fight against thanos.
Everyone was tired, Of everything.
They had gotten everyone back. Happiness surrounded...
body:
Avengers one-shot :)

It was the final fight against thanos.

Everyone was tired, Of everything.

They had gotten everyone back. Happiness surrounded the tension in the air.

Bucky was first to be back, Then Sam, Then Rhodey, Then T’challa.

Everyone.

Everyone was finally happy…

Not until the titan attacked again. Currently everyone’s lives were in danger again.

The fight would never stop.

“Steve this plan isn’t working so well!” Natasha shouted as she dodged a tree that Thanos threw at her.

“Improvise then!” Steve shouts back. He manages to punch Thanos’s arm.

Since everyone was back, The Avengers had a bigger chance of winning this time.

Peter Parker swung onto Thanos’ shoulders along with Mantis.

“That ain’t gonna work on me no more.” Thanos smacks the two clean off.

2/23

Okoye and T’challa work out a plan together and attack. Which also ends up in them getting thrown away.

4/23

Gamora, Drax, Peter Q and Groot, All shoot at the mad titan. All four of them getting blown away. Meanwhile Bucky had hold of Thanos’s Arm. Steve locked a solid punch onto the titans jaw. Tony blasted at him. The hulk and Thor helped Bucky out to keep Thanos down. The three failed.

A quick streak of electric blue light leaves everyone in confusion. Tony looks at Thor, Thor just shakes his head. It wasn’t him. The streak of light knocks Thanos down in an instant. The streak headed for Clint. Clint was tripped and was on his back.

His expressions went from confusion, wonder, Then happiness. A wide smile on his face grew and grew.

As the familiar phrase. “You didn’t see that coming?” Fills the air.
